reviewText: Considering the talent in this movie, CODE NAME CHAOS should have delivered more than a tepid, incoherent and lethargically acted movie.  It doesn't know whether it wants to be a comedy (it's not even funny) or some kind of espionage thriller.  Alice Krige, Brian Kerwin, Robert Loggia and David Warner are vapid and must have needed the money.  Don't waste your time.
